Chinese residents here visit Jonsung Revolutionary Museum 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- Chinese residents here visited the Jonsung Revolutionary Museum on July 2 on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the victory in the great Fatherland Liberation War.
 They looked round with deep emotion the house where President Kim Il Sung, the invincible and iron-willed commander, ratified the armistice agreement and the office room he used, a pit and other places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that they were very pleased to visit the museum associated with the immortal leadership history of the president, who led the war to a brilliant victory, on that occasion they resolved to contribute to boosting the Sino-Korean friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day officials of the Central Committee of the Association of Chinese Residents in Korea and Chinese here rendered assistance to the museum.

Kirgyz figure criticizes U.S. hostile policy toward DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- Klara Azhibekova, First Secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Kirgyzstan, on June 24 sent a letter of protest to Bush, denouncing the United States for its hostile policy toward the DPRK.
 Expressing deep concern over the U.S. hostile policy toward the DPRK, the letter said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Democratic People's Republic of Korea is a sovereign state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is impossible in the 21st century to solve international problems by force of arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The worldwide dismantlement of nuclear weapons and nuclear non-proliferation will bear due fruit when the U.S., a nuclear giant, sets an example in this field. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is an important work related to the destiny of the world and future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world progressive forces hope that the NATO will be dissolved of its own accord as was the case with the Warsaw treaty was organization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is a socialist country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The scenarios applied to Serbia and Montenegro and Iraq will not be workable in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We demand the U.S. take hands off Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter warned that Bush should have sound thinking power and not forget the past lesson of the U.S.

"Final results of investigation" published in S. Korea under fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- The "final results of investigation" conducted by the "special inspection team" in South Korea into what it called "remittance to the north" only betrayed its narrow-minded view on the nation and brought shame to it, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits a serious attention in the "results of investigation" is that the team deliberately linked the issue of "remittance to the north" to the historic Pyongyang summit meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is thanks to the June 15 Joint Declaration that the process of north-south reconciliation has made progress despite such vicious moves of the U.S. to invade the north and the "Grand National Party" and other political parties, organizations and people from all walks of life in South Korea have been able to escape from the disaster of war. And they still benefit from it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
No one can deny this reality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The attempt to link the issue of "remittance to the north" to the historic Pyongyang summit meeting is a foolish act which can be committed only by those who have neither political obligation nor an iota of conscience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "final results of investigation" are intolerable as they are an anti-historic and treacherous action to downplay the historic significance of the Pyongyang meeting on the strength of the "law on special inspection". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This case teaches a serious lesson that if one fails to properly judge and handle all the problems from a national stand, one will play into the hands of foreign forces and anti-reunification forces and put the inter-Korean relations into the danger of collapse. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic Pyongyang meeting recorded a brilliant page in the history of the movement for national reunification as it was a great undertaking that brought about a new turn in the movement. No one can play down its historic significance and great vitality even a bit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "results of investigation" are intolerable as they diametrically run counter to the vital interests of the nation.

Nomination of Kim Jong Il as candidate for SPA hailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- Papers here today editorially congratulate supreme commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il on his nomination as a candidate for the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK at the electorate meeting of constituency no. 649.
 Rodong Sinmun says that his nomination is a revelation of the unshakable faith and will of the servicemen and the people of Korea to have him at the head of the party, the state and the revolutionary armed forces forever, reliably defend the DPRK, a heritage left by President Kim Il Sung, and build a great prosperous socialist power in this land without fail under Kim Jong Il's Songun leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His nomination is an expression of profound reverence and absolute trust of the servicemen and the people in him, the paper says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the fruition of his outstanding leadership that the president's idea on state-building and his exploits have been firmly preserved and glorified despite the most difficult hardships in our country and the overall socialist construction is making brisk headway with the people's army as a hard core and a model. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His nomination is an expression of the absolute worship and enthusiastic reverence for him which have been cemented in actual life for a long time. His authority is unchallengeable today and tomorrow as he leads the revolution in the van with his matchless outstanding political ability, qualification and lofty virtues. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that his nomination is a striking manifestation of the fixed faith and will of the army and the people of Korea to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche to the last under his Songun revolutionary leadership.

No U.S. psychological operation will work on DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- The army and people of the DPRK are sure to emerge victorious in the fierce confrontation with the U.S. as long as they are led by Kim Jong Il, say papers here today in signed articles dedicated to the 20th anniversary of  President Kim Il Sung's famous work "Let Us Shatter Imperialist Moves Towards Aggression and War and Safeguard Peace and Independence."
 In the work the president laid bare the true colors of the U.S. imperialists keen to get world supremacy and called on all the peace-loving people of the world to concentrate the attack on the U.S. imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says that the revolutionary banner of independence against imperialism provided by the president has been held aloft by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il's Songun policy is a decisive factor of guaranteeing a final victory of the army and people of the DPRK in the confrontation with the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This policy is based on his determination to achieve a final victory in the life-and-death battle against the U.S. imperialists without fail and his strong national mettle to firmly defend the sovereignty and dignity of the nation with tremendous military power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK are stalwartly standing guard over the forefront in the struggle against the U.S.-led imperialists, overcoming all difficulties with revolutionary faith and will. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people have faith of sure victory and rare pluck that no one can defeat a people ready to die, high awareness to share their destiny with the headquarters of the revolution to the last and devotedly defend it in any adversity and strong principle and constancy not to abandon their revolutionary principle and conscience even though they have to subsist on gruel mixed with edible-grass, tightening their belts. Our revolutionary ranks are pervaded with this faith and will. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Neither sinister "horror strategy" nor cunning psychological operation and bribing and destabilizing operations on the part of the U.S. imperialists can ever cut ice with such army and people.

Patriotic activities of war veterans 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- War veterans of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea are devotedly working for the development and prosperity of the country with a high degree of consciousness as citizens.
 War veterans in South Hwanghae Province voluntarily formed more than 400 sapling-cultivation sub-work teams. Though old now, they are willing to live in the spirit with which they fought devotedly for the leader and the country during the last Korean War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The art agitation activities of war veterans brisk in all parts of the country reflect the noble spiritual world of the old men and women with a strong sense of patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the past 18 years since they formed an agitation squad for increased production and better and faster construction, women veterans in Waudo district, Nampho city, rendered assistance to army units and major projects on more than 100 occasions. In this period they gave some 3,000 art performances to inspire servicemen and builders. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the past five years war veterans in Haeju city conducted art agitation activities before more than 100,000 people on nearly 400 occasions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National art festivals of war veterans and honored disabled soldiers take place every year, giving impetus to their art agitation activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Theirs are not merely artistic activities but patriotic activities of forerunners in revolution who are trying to hand down to posterity heritage not material but ideological and spiritual.

Origin of Workers' Party of Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- The Workers' Party of Korea (WPK) has covered a long way replete with victory for scores of years since its foundation. it is entirely thanks to its deep roots provided by President Kim Il Sung.
 The president, with deep penetration into strife among factionalists and flunkeyists in the latter half of the 1920s, formed the society for rallying comrades, the first party organization in Korea, with revolutionaries of a new type who were not infected with factionalism or flunkeyism, on July 3, Juche 19 (1930). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK has grown from this party organization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The society was a revolutionary party organization guided by the Juche idea, and the mother body in organizing and expanding grass-roots organizations of the party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The formation of the society was the foundation of the first true party organization of the working class guided by the leader in Korea. As a result, the young communists of the new generation could have an organization of genuine revolutionary vanguards and make preparations to found the party under its unified guidance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Party organizations were expanded rapidly with the society as the parent body, the unified guidance system over them established well and the unity and cohesion of the revolutionary ranks behind President Kim Il Sung strengthened. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It made it possible to found the WPK in a short span of time right after the liberation of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was the faith and will of the president to start the revolution with the work of mustering men who would share the same destiny with him and to develop the revolution and achieve its final victory by constantly rallying more and more comrades. From this point of view, he named the first party organization the society for rallying comrades.

Kim Jong Il nominated as candidate for SPA at electorate meetings across DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- Electorate meetings took place at constituencies in different parts of the country to nominate candidates for deputies to the 11th Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK.
 The participants in the meetings nominated leader Kim Jong Il as a candidate for the SPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reporters and speakers at the meetings said that the upcoming election will be an event of great political significance as it will help further strengthen and develop the DPRK government to be a political weapon for upholding Kim Jong Il's Songun idea and leadership and strikingly demonstrate the might of the single-hearted unity in the DPRK, the advantages of the man-centred socialist system of Korean style and the invincible stamina of Juche Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporters courteously nominated Kim Jong Il as a candidate for the 11th SPA reflecting the ardent wish and unanimous desire of all the voters and people and the speakers and the voters fully supported and approved the proposals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meetings solemnly declared that Kim Jong Il has been nominated as a candidate for the SPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Letters to Kim Jong Il were adopted there.
